{"ts":"2026-06-27T06:09:11.264Z","type":"agent_event","event":{"type":"content_end","contentType":"reasoning","reasoning":"**Analyzing the Design**\n\nI'm focusing intently on the design, specifically the elegant dark theme and its impact. The CSS layout is really standing out, particularly the font-mono usage and custom colors like `#009DFF` and `#00FFC2`. I am also examining the impact of the use of `border-white/5` and how it works with the other elements. The filters and table column designs are excellent.\n\n\n**Designing the AI Command Center**\n\nI'm now deep-diving into the `/admin/ai-operations` page. I'm imagining it as a secure, simulated command center for Dr. Vance. I've formulated a design plan, framing it as an \"enterprise command bridge\" with dark, premium widgets and high-fidelity status indicators. I'm aiming for a high-fidelity, interactive glass cockpit feel. The emphasis is on global oversight and clear telemetry, like a modern, simulated control panel.\n\n\n**Crafting the Command Center**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the layout of the AI command center, focusing on the Sovereign Observability Badge and how to make the split layout effective. The status rails and health metric cards are also being worked on, specifically the interactive agents table, which demands searching and filtering options. My plan is for a real-time Governance Alerts Ledger and the interactive Enclave Core Telemetry Stream, which opens when selecting an agent row. The final touch will be the header section.\n\n\n**Developing the Interface**\n\nI'm now iterating on the design details for the `/admin/ai-operations` page. I'm focusing on key UI elements. I've conceptualized a Sandbox Notice Alert banner and a 4-column Observability Metrics Grid for critical KPIs, with associated status rail indicators. I'm also planning a dynamic Control Bar with filters and a Master-Detail Board for agent management, with overlay actions. This work is based on an \"enterprise command bridge\" feel.\n\n\n**Refining the Alerts Panel**\n\nI'm now zeroing in on the Governance Alerts Panel, considering placement alongside the agents table, perhaps a 3-column or collapsible layout for maximum impact. I am thinking of interactive options for viewing thread logs. I'm focusing on making the UI feel complex and tactical.\n\n**Exploring Interaction Tactics**\n\nI am now thinking deeply about the interaction strategy, refining how users will interact with the new interface. I'm focusing on row selection, owner assignment, filters, and micro-animations to enhance the user experience. I envision a dynamic telemetry detail drawer. I'm considering an inline dropdown for owner assignment and real-time filtering.\n\n\n"}}
