e \"Change Assignee\" selector within the Detail Drawer with custom labels and immediate state feedback. I've successfully added local-only actions to assign owners. I'm also now planning the implementation of a \"Governance Alerts Widget.\" I want an aligned board for alerts, either alongside or beneath the agent table, incorporating its own filters or tying to the master ones.\n\n\n**Adding Agent Operations**\n\nI'm now adding operation buttons to the agent operations table, starting with an \"Assign Owner\" dropdown that updates the parent state seamlessly. Next, I'm working on the \"Trigger Thread Dump\" button, which will display a loader and then append a mock log. I'm also adding a \"Verify Integrity\" button and incorporating a monospaced log window. Finally, I'm adding an external link to project details.\n\n\n**Revising Mock Data**\n\nI'm now revising my approach to mock data. I realized I need to stick precisely to the standardized data in `lib/mock-data-model.ts` to maintain consistency and avoid generating new, unverified mock elements. This includes using the existing client names and dashboard numbers, and extending those. The goal is to avoid inventing new clients or logos, and instead, maintain this mock standard.\n\n\n"}}
